{"type":"message","id":"f2709f64","parentId":"94fdd2e6","timestamp":"2026-05-16T08:56:12.817Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The feishu-doc skill doesn't support bitable operations. Let me check if there's another skill or tool for Feishu bitable. I should look for feishu-wiki or similar. Actually, looking at the available skills, I see feishu-wiki, feishu-drive, feishu-perm, etc. - but no feishu-bitable directly. Let me search for bitable-related tools.\n\nActually, I remember that the feishu plugin in OpenClaw likely has bitable support through the message tool or some other tool. But the skill.md only covers doc operations. \n\nFor bitable (飞书多维表) operations, I might need to use exec with curl directly against the Feishu API. But that would require the access token. Let me think...\n \nThe user is asking if I can fetch the latest data after they modified the spreadsheet headers. Since there's no dedicated bitable skill available and feishu-doc only handles document operations, I'll need to try the message tool to see if it has any bitable capabilities, otherwise I'll need to explain this limitation.\n","thinkingSignature":"0135e8d9a8ff2acffb1cfbcf24c8369a32af8fe80a68390e177a3f974ef22f46"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6mt7nv9gu4kr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /home/halei/.openclaw/plugin-skills/feishu-wiki/ && cat /home/halei/.openclaw/plugin-skills/feishu-wiki/SKILL.md 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":291,"output":303,"cacheRead":40000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40594,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778921763135,"responseId":"06576423057cb57b7fda3ccf9e6f0eea"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b460fff7","parentId":"f2709f64","timestamp":"2026-05-16T08:56:12.839Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6mt7nv9gu4kr_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"SKILL.md\n---\nname: feishu-wiki\ndescription: |\n  Feishu knowledge base navigation. Activate when user mentions knowledge base, wiki, or wiki links.\n---\n\n# Feishu Wiki Tool\n\nSingle tool `feishu_wiki` for knowledge base operations.\n\n## Token Extraction\n\nFrom URL `https://xxx.feishu.cn/wiki/ABC123def` → `token` = `ABC123def`\n\n## Actions\n\n### List Knowledge Spaces\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"spaces\" }\n```\n\nReturns all accessible wiki spaces.\n\n### List Nodes\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"nodes\", \"space_id\": \"7xxx\" }\n```\n\nWith parent:\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"nodes\", \"space_id\": \"7xxx\", \"parent_node_token\": \"wikcnXXX\" }\n```\n\n### Get Node Details\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"get\", \"token\": \"***\" }\n```\n\nReturns: `node_token`, `obj_token`, `obj_type`, etc. Use `obj_token` with `feishu_doc` to read/write the document.\n\n### Create Node\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"create\", \"space_id\": \"7xxx\", \"title\": \"New Page\" }\n```\n\nWith type and parent:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"create\",\n  \"space_id\": \"7xxx\",\n  \"title\": \"Sheet\",\n  \"obj_type\": \"sheet\",\n  \"parent_node_token\": \"wikcnXXX\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"SKILL.md\n---\nname: feishu-wiki\ndescription: |\n  Feishu knowledge base navigation. Activate when user mentions knowledge base, wiki, or wiki links.\n---\n\n# Feishu Wiki Tool\n\nSingle tool `feishu_wiki` for knowledge base operations.\n\n## Token Extraction\n\nFrom URL `https://xxx.feishu.cn/wiki/ABC123def` → `token` = `ABC123def`\n\n## Actions\n\n### List Knowledge Spaces\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"spaces\" }\n```\n\nReturns all accessible wiki spaces.\n\n### List Nodes\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"nodes\", \"space_id\": \"7xxx\" }\n```\n\nWith parent:\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"nodes\", \"space_id\": \"7xxx\", \"parent_node_token\": \"wikcnXXX\" }\n```\n\n### Get Node Details\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"get\", \"token\": \"ABC123def\" }\n```\n\nReturns: `node_token`, `obj_token`, `obj_type`, etc. Use `obj_token` with `feishu_doc` to read/write the document.\n\n### Create Node\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"create\", \"space_id\": \"7xxx\", \"title\": \"New Page\" }\n```\n\nWith type and parent:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"create\",\n  \"space_id\": \"7xxx\",\n  \"title\": \"Sheet\",\n  \"obj_type\": \"sheet\",\n  \"parent_node_token\": \"wikcnXXX\"\n}","cwd":"/home/halei/workspace-tts"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778921772839}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c1a9862","parentId":"b460fff7","timestamp":"2026-05-16T08:56:20.999Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The feishu-wiki skill mentions `feishu_doc` for document read/write. But I need to understand if there's a separate skill for \"bitable\" (多维表) operations. Looking at the feishu plugin, maybe it supports bitable through the `feishu_doc` skill or a separate skill.\n\nActually, looking back at the conversation history, when I successfully wrote to the Feishu table, I was using some tool. Let me search for what tool was used to write to the table.\n\nActually I realize: the user is asking if I can fetch the latest table data now that they've modified the headers. I need to find a way to read the bitable. Let me check what the feishu plugin supports for bitable.\n","thinkingSignature":"de397ad2fe1ebb93c89edf83f83de3201f02341affe8dfc89250198908cfeabb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xgrwyk7qnfrz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"bitable\\|多维表\" /home/halei/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xgrwyk7qnfrz_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"bitable\\|base.*table\" /home/halei/.openclaw/npm/node_modules/@openclaw/feishu/dist/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":434,"output":271,"cacheRead":40256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40961,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778921772871,"responseId":"0657642d8baee1a526815acc8bf285a4"}}
