{"type":"message","id":"7e88292d","parentId":"423834f1","timestamp":"2026-05-16T08:57:43.699Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the feishu channel is up and running. But I'm getting confused about what tools I have available. Let me think more carefully about what I can do.\n\nLooking at the memory, the feishu bitable was being accessed via the feishu plugin. The memory mentions a tool \"feishu_bitable_get_meta\" which can read the fields/headers. But I don't know if this tool is actually loaded and available in the current runtime.\n\nLet me look at the agent configuration to understand what tools are available. From the session_status output, I can see there are 10 agents.\n\nActually, I think the simpler approach is to just try to read the current table structure using the feishu API, since I know the app credentials from the config. Let me try with curl directly.\n\nActually, wait - I should look at this differently. I know the feishu bitable URL from the context: https://bytedance.feishu.cn/base/AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd?table=tblHU2do30jzinJT\n\n\nAnd the tts account has credentials I can work with. Rather than continuing to search for the right tool, I should just test the API call directly to fetch the current table fields and see what structure we're working with.\n","thinkingSignature":"901b364d854eec7a662745a3989758cd2d19105ee6d1307ced37ea12d22cfb20"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p8te5g90amq4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/halei/workspace-tts && node -e \"\nconst https = require('https');\n\nconst appId = 'cli_a930f78f51399bc6';\nconst appSecret = 'sWYftqexDF2zr6I36ofoyhSz8rLxThbY';\nconst appToken = 'AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd';\nconst tableId = 'tblHU2do30jzinJT';\n\nfunction request(method, path, body, token) {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const options = {\n      hostname: 'open.feishu.cn',\n      path: '/open-apis/auth/v3/app_access_token/internal',\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }\n    };\n    const req = https.request(options, res => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', d => data += d);\n      res.on('end', () => resolve(JSON.parse(data)));\n    });\n    req.on('error', reject);\n    req.write(JSON.stringify({ app_id: appId, app_secret: appSecret }));\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  const at = await request('POST', '/open-apis/auth/v3/app_access_token/internal', { app_id: appId, app_secret: appSecret });\n  const token = at.app_access_token;\n  console.log('Token OK:', token ? 'yes' : 'no');\n  \n  // Get fields\n  const fieldsRes = await new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const options = {\n      hostname: 'open.feishu.cn',\n      path: \\`/open-apis/bitable/v1/apps/\\${appToken}/tables/\\${tableId}/fields\\`,\n      method: 'GET',\n      headers: { Authorization: \\`Bearer \\${token}\\` }\n    };\n    const req = https.request(options, res => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', d => data += d);\n      res.on('end', () => resolve(JSON.parse(data)));\n    });\n    req.on('error', reject);\n    req.end();\n  });\n  console.log('Fields:', JSON.stringify(fieldsRes.data?.items || [], null, 2));\n}\n\nmain().catch(console.error);\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":710,"output":785,"cacheRead":43328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44823,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778921845984,"responseId":"06576476a35aa54944c5f2c465dd3474"}}
